So many polarizing opinions as always. I think it makes the bundesliga more interesting if multiple teams have the potential to earn the trophy. That's why I love what Xabi did in Leverkusen. He made the bundesliga interesting again. For once it's not clear who's going to win this year.  Concerning the game. It showed that Kompany made Bayern strong again and that they are stronger in controlling the game then Leverkusen but it also showed that Leverkusen can stand against the best. I love that. It was also tactically interesting. Bayern rarely made it into the penalty area, and Leverkusen rarely made it out. I think the constant high pressing from Kompany was the reason why Leverkusen never really got into the offensive, in that regard Bayern was better. If Leverkusen had gotten more control, they would have gotten more chances, but also more counters against them. I couldn't say who would have won then, but it would probably create more goals and make it a bit more interesting for the average viewer.  That's my take. Both teams play awesome football and I'm looking forward to see both playing in the Bundesliga but also in the Champions league. We've rarely had so good a chance of having multiple german teams in the k.o. stage of the CL!
